                    </div>
                    <div class="about_Left">
                        <p>Nada Dhyana is from the inspiration of <strong>Dr. Sri Ganapathi Sachchidhananda Swamiji (fondly called Sri Swamiji) and Sri Datta Vijayananda Teertha Swamiji (fondly called as Sri Bala Swamiji) of Avadhoota Datta Peetham</strong>. Through Datta Kriya Yoga <a href="https://www.dattakriyayoga.or" target="_blank">(https://www.dattakriyayoga.org)</a> as certified teachers, they contribute to the community by systematically incorporating a life-style of simple practices.</p>


                        <p>Sri Swamiji has blended Vyayamas – flow movements with breath, Pranayama, Mudras, Meditation & Nada Chikitsha – healing with Music. 
                        Datta Kriya Yoga is an ancient yogic tradition of India prescribed by Sri Swamiji to silence the mind and attain a state of being able to attain a state of equanimity.</p>
                        
                        
                        <p>With every thought or movement, the breath pattern changes. Without this change in breath, the action cannot be fulfilled. By developing the ability to control the breath, by practice of Pranayama – where we regulate the flow of breath, we open our self-healing power from within at the level of body and mind.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
              <br><br><br>
             <div class="about_row">
                <div class="about_Left">
                    <p><strong>Datta Kriya Yoga</strong> combines Vyayamas – gentle flow yogic moves with breath, and healing power of music. This results in a natural state of meditation taking oneself beyond states of pain and stresses of mind.</p>
                    <p><strong>Sri Swamiji</strong> is a pioneer in healing music. His personal research of more than 50 years and experiments with music's therapeutic powers led to the conviction that the healing powers of music should be available to everyone.</p>
                </div>
